$interpreted: Diana: What happened to him!? How did he get hurt like this!?
Panicked Athlete: A bunch of people just ran into the room. They didn't say a word, they just started charging at us!
Panicked Athlete: First they knocked out all the guys who were supposed to be watching the captain, and then they starting beating on him!
Nolva: How in the...
Diana: I can't believe they would go to such lengths...
Team Captain: It's fine, I'm not hurt all that bad. I can still make it to the crab run tomorrow! I'll show them!
Team Captain: Yagh... How come I can't move!?
Diana: That's enough.
Team Captain: It's fine, I'm just a bit numb is all. Come on foot, move!!
Diana: I said that's enough!
Diana: You said it before, an injured team member can't participate! Well, you're injured, so I'm ordering you to sit this one out!
Team Captain: But, but... ah, dammit!! We were so close, too!
Diana: I know how you must feel... Don't worry, I'll make this right.
Kittyeyes: But we don't have anyone else who can compete!
Diana: I can compete!
Diana: I started this, so let me be the one to end it!
Announcer: Ladies and gentlemen, after a night of rest, we're here at the final event... the crab run!!
Nolva: That crab doesn't look too happy... Diana, are you sure this is okay?
Kittyeyes: Let's just trust Diana, Nolva.
Diana: Crabbie, I know you're not too happy about this, but we have to fight!
Diana: If you were willing to do this with the captain, then please, for him, let's do this together!
Nolva: It worked!
Jerome: Please be careful, Diana!
Diana: Let's run!
Monkey Boy: Hmph, they've sure got team spirit.
Ape Crab Runner: Don't worry, boss. Those outsiders don't know how to crab run! They'll eat my dust!!
Monkey Boy: Hmph, I guess you're right. I mean, if that broad really took the win, I just dunno...
Ape Crab Runner: The run's starting, captain. I've gotta go.
Monkey Boy: Now, let the games begin.

Announcer: Seems like everyone is on their mark!
Alright, let the crab run begin~~
Ape Crab Runner: Alright, Cra-bro, it's time to end this! Special move—Screw Shot!
Announcer: And there it is, folks, the Rapaging Ape's ultimate crab technique, strongest in the Oasis... the Screw Shot!!
Diana: Let's do it, Crabbie!
Announcer: W-Wow! She dodged it!!
Announcer: Diana somehow managed to perform the legendary Desert Dash technique, incredible!!
Diana: Desert Dash, huh?
Diana: Alright, then! Let's do this, Crabbie!
Monkey Boy: Gyah... You asked for it, you meddling tourists!!
Ape Crab Runner: Wha... She's caught up!?
Diana: It's the last turn just up ahead, Crabbie! Let's take the lead!
Monkey Boy: Wait 'til just before she gets here, then drop the stone on her!
Jerome: Not so fast!!
Monkey Boy: What!?
Kittyeyes: We should have taught these jerks a lesson ages ago!
Kittyeyes: Say, Jerome, I really didn't think you'd be up to using these sort of backhanded tactics.
Jerome: If he were to compete fairly, then I'd play fair, too. But if he wants to bend the rules, then I'm all for it.
Monkey Boy: Yah... I won't lose!
Kittyeyes: Hmph, jerks like you never learn your lesson!
Diana: It's the final turn! Let's do it... the Desert Dash!!
Ape Crab Runner: Get her, Cra-bro! Screw Shot!
Announcer: They've reached the end!!!
Announcer: And the winner of the crab run is...
Announcer: Glory of the Oasis' Diana and Crabbie!!
Announcer: Congratulations to Glory of the Oasis with their 30 points! They're the winners of the competition!!
Team Captain: We... we really did it. Thank you... thank you so much.
Diana: Don't thank me, this was everybody's effort!
Diana: But you deserve the trophy, captain!
Diana: I hope you can use this to motivate all of the Oasis athletes once more.
Team Captain: I will!
Team Captain: Alright team, let's go tell everybody we won!!
Kittyeyes: Is that really okay? What if that monkey tries to get revenge?
Diana: Don't worry, I've already sent some people to take care of him.
Diana: So, what do you all plan to do next?
Kittyeyes: Hmm~ I'd love to stay here a bit longer, but I think Roger would start to worry if I didn't go back soon.
Nolva: Yeah, we should be getting back.
Jerome: I have to get back to the kingdom, too.
Diana: Is that so...
Diana: Well, Kittyeyes, Nolva, Jerome... I truly enjoyed our time together. Thank you.
Diana: I always thought I had to stay put, that everyone needed me... But you've all shown me that I can take a break now and then.
Diana: If you ever want to come to the Desert Kingdom for a visit, just let me know. I'll be sure to show you around!
Kittyeyes: I'll hold ya to it!
Nolva: Wait, I just had an idea...
Nolva: I think they're giving out some special wine to celebrate the end of the competition. Why don't we all share a drink tonight?
Kittyeyes: Heyy~ Good idea! Let's do it!
Diana: What about you, Jerome?
Jerome: How could I say no?
Diana: Well then, the first round's on me!
Kittyeyes: Diana~
